The paper is about building recommender systems, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The paper proposes a neural network model for item-based collaborative filtering, which involves learning item similarities from data, and hence falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of attention networks, which are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories.
